{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, if the ontology presents biased data, inconsistent or incorrect definitions, relationships, or concepts, it can lead to errors in the interpretable representations.",
    "This section relies on the results of our review to identify important issues that limit the ability of transformers in handling longitudinal health data.",
    "Therefore, we summarize such issues and discuss initial efforts that we have identified to address them.",
    "This review shows that clinical-based sparse electronic health records are the main multifeatured longitudinal data source for transformers in the health domain (Sect. 4.3).",
    "However, only a few classes of features (e.g., medication and diagnosis codes) have been considered at the same time thus far."
  ]
}